							<path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-width="2"
							      d="M9.879 16.121A3 3 0 1012.015 11L11 14H9c0 .768.293 1.536.879 2.121z"/>
						</svg>
					</div>
					<h3 class="text-xl font-bold text-primary mb-4 text-center">Burning Smell</h3>
					<p class="text-darkgray mb-4">
						A burning smell coming from your heating system could indicate an electrical problem or overheating
						components. Turn off your system immediately and call for emergency service to prevent fire hazards.
					</p>
				</div>

				<!-- Unusual Noises -->
				<div class="bg-white p-8 rounded-lg shadow-md">
					<div class="w-16 h-16 bg-secondary rounded-full flex items-center justify-center mb-6 mx-auto">
						<svg xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" class="h-8 w-8 text-white" fill="none" viewBox="0 0 24 24"
						     stroke="currentColor">
							<path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-width="2"
							      d="M15.536 8.464a5 5 0 010 7.072m2.828-9.9a9 9 0 010 12.728M5.586 15.536a5 5 0 017.072 0m-9.9-2.828a9 9 0 0112.728 0"/>
						</svg>
					</div>
					<h3 class="text-xl font-bold text-primary mb-4 text-center">Loud or Unusual Noises</h3>
					<p class="text-darkgray mb-4">
						Grinding, screeching, banging, or other loud noises from your heating system often indicate a serious
						mechanical problem that could cause further damage if not addressed immediately.
					</p>
				</div>

				<!-- Gas Odor -->
				<div class="bg-white p-8 rounded-lg shadow-md">
					<div class="w-16 h-16 bg-secondary rounded-full flex items-center justify-center mb-6 mx-auto">
						<svg xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" class="h-8 w-8 text-white" fill="none" viewBox="0 0 24 24"
						     stroke="currentColor">
							<path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-width="2"
							      d="M12 9v2m0 4h.01m-6.938 4h13.856c1.54 0 2.502-1.667 1.732-3L13.732 4c-.77-1.333-2.694-1.333-3.464 0L3.34 16c-.77 1.333.192 3 1.732 3z"/>
						</svg>
					</div>
					<h3 class="text-xl font-bold text-primary mb-4 text-center">Gas Odor</h3>
					<p class="text-darkgray mb-4">
						If you smell gas near your furnace, leave your home immediately and call both your gas company and our
						emergency service from a safe location. Gas leaks pose serious safety risks and require immediate
						professional attention.
					</p>
				</div>

				<!-- Carbon Monoxide Alarm -->
				<div class="bg-white p-8 rounded-lg shadow-md">
					<div class="w-16 h-16 bg-secondary rounded-full flex items-center justify-center mb-6 mx-auto">
						<svg xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" class="h-8 w-8 text-white" fill="none" viewBox="0 0 24 24"
						     stroke="currentColor">
							<path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-width="2"
							      d="M12 9v2m0 4h.01m-6.938 4h13.856c1.54 0 2.502-1.667 1.732-3L13.732 4c-.77-1.333-2.694-1.333-3.464 0L3.34 16c-.77 1.333.192 3 1.732 3z"/>
						</svg>
					</div>
					<h3 class="text-xl font-bold text-primary mb-4 text-center">Carbon Monoxide Alarm</h3>
					<p class="text-darkgray mb-4">
						If your carbon monoxide detector is sounding, evacuate your home immediately and call for emergency service.
						Carbon monoxide is a colorless, odorless gas that can be deadly. A malfunctioning heating system can be a
						source of carbon monoxide.
					</p>
				</div>

				<!-- Electrical Issues -->
				<div class="bg-white p-8 rounded-lg shadow-md">
					<div class="w-16 h-16 bg-secondary rounded-full flex items-center justify-center mb-6 mx-auto">
						<svg xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" class="h-8 w-8 text-white" fill="none" viewBox="0 0 24 24"
